title: For Sale:  NEW Flat-Top AR-15 / M-4 with Quad-rail Gas Block!!!
postcontent:
This AR-15 / M-4 has a flawless Aero Precision lower (I just changed to it, but the pictures don't yet reflect the new lower.) with a Rock River Arms parts set in it, as well as a Rock River Arms 6-position collapsible stock.  I installed a Hogue rubber grip on it (if you have not used a rifle with a Hogue grip, you don't know what you are missing!).

The upper is an Anchor-Harvey flat-top with a Picatinny rail system that has numbered stations so that if you remove an optic, you can easily replace it at exactly the same spot.  It comes with an M-4 style detachable carry handle/rear sight.

I have also installed a MagPul MOE front handguard.  It is the beefy one that they made before they started making the thinner ones that fit over gas-piston systems.

The upper has a quad-rail gas block so that any optic you mount to the flat-top upper will not be staring into the back of the fixed front sight post!  This quad-rail gas block also allows the mounting of virtually anything you would like to it: lasers, lights, custom sling mounts (either bottom or side), and even bi-pods.  You can also mount a pop-up front iron sight on it as well. 

Speaking of slings, this weapon comes with a black nylon G.I. sling and a ProMag Picatinny Rail Sling Mount.

Of course it has the flash suppressor that doubles as a compensator (since the bottom is solid instead of having openings in it).  This also keeps the muzzle blast from kicking up so much dust if you are firing it from the prone position. 

THIS WEAPONS IS NEW AND UNFIRED.  I bought the lower and upper separate and put them together myself, then installed the Hogue rubber grip and the MagPul handguard.  I did this because I couldn't find all of those features on any complete gun under $1000. 

This is my personal AR, but I am willing to part with it because I need the cash.  I am only asking $775 for it.  If you have any questions or want any other pics, please let me know.

  - Curtis

The extended magazine on the 590sp guarantees that you are not going to run out of shells before the fight is over. The gun has a reasonable kick that a wife can handle and if you live in close quarters, the only thing you want protecting you house is a shot gun.
